pnniRouteAddrAdvertisingNodeId.description: The node ID of a node advertising reachability to the address prefix. If the local node index is zero, then the advertising node ID must be set to all zeros.

pnniRouteAddrAdvertisedPortId.name: pnniRouteAddrAdvertisedPortId
pnniRouteAddrAdvertisedPortId.description: The port identifier used from the advertising node to reach the given address prefix.

pnniRouteAddrType.name: pnniRouteAddrType
pnniRouteAddrType.description: The type (e.g. internal or exterior) of reachability from the advertising node to the address prefix. Reject(2) refers to an address prefix which, if matched, indicates that the message should be discarded as unreachable. This is used in some protocols as a means of correctly aggregating routes.

pnniRouteAddrProto.name: pnniRouteAddrProto
pnniRouteAddrProto.description: The routing mechanism via which the connectivity from the advertising node to the reachable address prefix was learned.

pnniRouteAddrPnniScope.name: pnniRouteAddrPnniScope
pnniRouteAddrPnniScope.description: The PNNI scope of advertisement (i.e. level of PNNI hierarchy) of the reachability from the advertising node to the address prefix.

pnniRouteAddrVPCapability.name: pnniRouteAddrVPCapability
pnniRouteAddrVPCapability.description: Indicates whether VPCs can be established from the advertising node to the reachable address prefix.

pnniRouteAddrMetricsTag.name: pnniRouteAddrMetricsTag
pnniRouteAddrMetricsTag.description: The index into the pnniMetricsTable for the traffic parameter values that apply for the connectivity from the advertising node to the reachable address prefix. There will be one or more entries in the pnniMetricsTable whose first instance identifier matches the value of this variable. If there are no parameters associated with this reachable address prefix then the distinguished value zero is used.

pnniRouteAddrPtseId.name: pnniRouteAddrPtseId
pnniRouteAddrPtseId.description: For reachable addresses learned via PNNI, this attribute contains the value of the PTSE Identifier for the PTSE being originated by the originating node which contains the information group(s) describing the reachable address. For reachable addresses learned by means other than PNNI, this attribute is set to zero.

pnniRouteAddrOriginateAdvertisement.name: pnniRouteAddrOriginateAdvertisement
pnniRouteAddrOriginateAdvertisement.description: Whether or not the reachable address specified by this entry is to be advertised by the local node into its PNNI routing domain. This object may only take on the value 'true' when the value of the corresponding instance of pnniRouteAddrProto is other than 'pnni'.

pnniRouteAddrInfo.name: pnniRouteAddrInfo
pnniRouteAddrInfo.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the particular routing protocol which is responsible for this reachable address prefix, as determined by the value specified in the route's pnniRouteAddrProto value. If this information is not present, its value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER zeroDotZero.

pnniRouteAddrOperStatus.name: pnniRouteAddrOperStatus
pnniRouteAddrOperStatus.description: Indicates whether the reachable address prefix is operationally valid and whether it is being advertised by this node.

pnniRouteAddrTimeStamp.name: pnniRouteAddrTimeStamp
pnniRouteAddrTimeStamp.description: Indicates when the connectivity from the advertising node to the reachable address prefix became known to the local node.

pnniRouteAddrRowStatus.name: pnniRouteAddrRowStatus
pnniRouteAddrRowStatus.description: To create, delete, activate and de-activate a reachable address prefix.

pnniRouteTnsTable.name: pnniRouteTnsTable
pnniRouteTnsTable.description: A table containing all the attributes necessary to determine what transit networks the PNNI entity believes are reachable and to determine which nodes are advertising this reachability. This table is also used to add static routes to reachable transit networks. The local node index which received the reachability information, type of network identification, network identification plan, transit network identifier, and an index that distinguishes between multiple listings of connectivity to a given transit network from a given local node are combined to form an instance ID for this object.

pnniRouteTnsEntry.name: pnniRouteTnsEntry
pnniRouteTnsEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a reachable transit network.

pnniRouteTnsType.name: pnniRouteTnsType
pnniRouteTnsType.description: The type of network identification used for this transit network.

pnniRouteTnsPlan.name: pnniRouteTnsPlan
pnniRouteTnsPlan.description: The network identification plan according to which network identification has been assigned.

pnniRouteTnsId.name: pnniRouteTnsId
pnniRouteTnsId.description: The value of the transit network identifier.

pnniRouteTnsIndex.name: pnniRouteTnsIndex
pnniRouteTnsIndex.description: An index into the set of listings of connectivity to a given transit network from a given local node.

pnniRouteTnsIfIndex.name: pnniRouteTnsIfIndex
pnniRouteTnsIfIndex.description: The local interface over which the transit network can be reached. The value zero indicates an unknown interface or reachability through a remote node. This object may only have a non-zero value if the value of the corresponding instance of pnniRouteTnsProto is other than 'pnni' and the node identified by pnniRouteTnsAdvertisingNodeId is instantiated within this switching system.

pnniRouteTnsAdvertisingNodeId.name: pnniRouteTnsAdvertisingNodeId
pnniRouteTnsAdvertisingNodeId.description: The node ID of a node advertising reachability to the transit network. If the local node index is zero, then the advertising node ID must also be set to zero.

pnniRouteTnsAdvertisedPortId.name: pnniRouteTnsAdvertisedPortId
pnniRouteTnsAdvertisedPortId.description: The port identifier used from the advertising node to reach the given transit network.

pnniRouteTnsRouteType.name: pnniRouteTnsRouteType
pnniRouteTnsRouteType.description: The type (e.g. exterior or other) of reachability from the advertising node to the transit network.

pnniRouteTnsProto.name: pnniRouteTnsProto
pnniRouteTnsProto.description: The routing mechanism via which the connectivity from the advertising node to the transit network was learned.

pnniRouteTnsPnniScope.name: pnniRouteTnsPnniScope
pnniRouteTnsPnniScope.description: The PNNI scope of advertisement (i.e. level of PNNI hierarchy) of the reachability from the advertising node to the transit network.

pnniRouteTnsVPCapability.name: pnniRouteTnsVPCapability
pnniRouteTnsVPCapability.description: Indicates whether VPCs can be established from the advertising node to the reachable transit network.

pnniRouteTnsMetricsTag.name: pnniRouteTnsMetricsTag
pnniRouteTnsMetricsTag.description: The index into the pnniMetricsTable for the traffic parameter values that apply for the connectivity from the advertising node to the transit network. There will be one or more entries in the pnniMetricsTable whose first instance identifier matches the value of this variable. If there are no parameters associated with this transit network then the distinguished value zero is used.

pnniRouteTnsPtseId.name: pnniRouteTnsPtseId
pnniRouteTnsPtseId.description: For reachable transit networks learned via PNNI, this attribute contains the value of the PTSE Identifier for the PTSE being originated by the originating node which contains the information group(s) describing the transit network. For reachable transit networks learned by means other than PNNI, this attribute is set to zero.

pnniRouteTnsOriginateAdvertisement.name: pnniRouteTnsOriginateAdvertisement
pnniRouteTnsOriginateAdvertisement.description: Whether or not the transit network specified by this entry is to be advertised by the local node into its PNNI routing domain. This object may only take on the value 'true' when the value of the corresponding instance of pnniRouteNodeProto is other than 'pnni'.

pnniRouteTnsInfo.name: pnniRouteTnsInfo
pnniRouteTnsInfo.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the particular routing protocol which is responsible for this transit network, as determined by the value specified in the route's pnniRouteTnsProto value. If this information is not present, its value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER zeroDotZero.

pnniRouteTnsOperStatus.name: pnniRouteTnsOperStatus
pnniRouteTnsOperStatus.description: Indicates whether the reachable transit network is operationally valid and whether it is being advertised by this node.

pnniRouteTnsTimeStamp.name: pnniRouteTnsTimeStamp
pnniRouteTnsTimeStamp.description: Indicates how long the connectivity from the advertising node to the reachable transit network has been known to the local node.

pnniRouteTnsRowStatus.name: pnniRouteTnsRowStatus
pnniRouteTnsRowStatus.description: To create, delete, activate and de-activate a reachable transit network.

pnniMIBCompliance.name: pnniMIBCompliance
pnniMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the PNNI MIB. Groups of PNNI objects required for management of a minimum function node are identified by the suffix MinGroup. Groups of PNNI objects required for management of a border node are identified by the suffix BorderGroup. Groups of PNNI objects required for management of a PGL/LGN capable node are identified by the suffix LgnGroup. Groups of optional PNNI objects are identified by the suffix OptionalGroup.

pnniGeneralMinGroup.name: pnniGeneralMinGroup
pnniGeneralMinGroup.description: A collection of general PNNI objects required for management of a minimum function switching system.

pnniGeneralBorderGroup.name: pnniGeneralBorderGroup
pnniGeneralBorderGroup.description: A collection of general PNNI objects required for management of a border node.

pnniNodeMinGroup.name: pnniNodeMinGroup
pnniNodeMinGroup.description: A collection of per node PNNI objects required for management of a minimum function switching system.

pnniNodePglMinGroup.name: pnniNodePglMinGroup
pnniNodePglMinGroup.description: A collection of per node PGL election related PNNI objects required for management of a minimum function switching system.

pnniNodePglLgnGroup.name: pnniNodePglLgnGroup
pnniNodePglLgnGroup.description: A collection of per node PGL election related PNNI objects required for management of a PGL/LGN capable switching system.

pnniNodeTimerMinGroup.name: pnniNodeTimerMinGroup
pnniNodeTimerMinGroup.description: A collection of per node PNNI objects required for management of timers and significant change thresholds in a minimum function switching system.

pnniNodeTimerLgnGroup.name: pnniNodeTimerLgnGroup
pnniNodeTimerLgnGroup.description: A collection of per node PNNI objects required for management of timers in a PGL/LGN capable switching system.

pnniNodeSvccLgnGroup.name: pnniNodeSvccLgnGroup
pnniNodeSvccLgnGroup.description: A collection of per node SVCC-based RCC related PNNI objects required for management of a PGL/LGN capable switching system.

pnniScopeMinGroup.name: pnniScopeMinGroup
pnniScopeMinGroup.description: A collection of per node scope mapping related PNNI objects required for management of a minimum function switching system.

pnniSummaryLgnGroup.name: pnniSummaryLgnGroup
pnniSummaryLgnGroup.description: A collection of PNNI objects required for controlling address summarization.

pnniSummaryAddressLgnGroup.name: pnniSummaryAddressLgnGroup
pnniSummaryAddressLgnGroup.description: A collection of PNNI objects required for controlling address summarization.

pnniIfMinGroup.name: pnniIfMinGroup
pnniIfMinGroup.description: A collection of per interface PNNI objects required for management of a minimum function switching system.
